My goddess initiation in Egypt was the most powerful trip of 2022. From climbing into pyramids, to riding camels across the Sahara desert, to cruising on the Nile River, it was a country of so much history and mystery. I came back so fierce and have never felt so comfortable and happy being authentically me. 🦄💖

The most liberating trip of 2022 was my solo adventure to #Dubai. Where I got to glam to the fullest, drove a Rolls Royce and Lamborghini through the most expensive real estate and shopping centers in the world, and went #skydiving over the #PalmIsland. I love to travel and experience life to the fullest, but I truly am so happy that I feel at home in the tech-immersed Silicon Valley. Looking forward to an epic 2023 with more badass moments with the badasses in my life. #beyondblessed #lovemylove #grounded #fullheart

In just 2 days, I’ll be in #anaheim for my very first panel interview at one of the largest medical design and manufacturing events! I’ve had experience interviewing Hollywood actors in the past, but now I’ll be in the hot seat and will be asked the questions! Yikes! 😱 Besides the nerves I’m feeling, it’s truly an honor to share the stage with so many other AMAZING women in manufacturing to share our knowledge and passion. If any of you will be at #MDMwest, please come by for a listen and say hi.  #manufacturing #womeninmanufacturing #womenin3dprinting #womeninmedtech

It has been 6 years since I’ve had a microphone in my hand and like I had mentioned in my last post, I was extremely nervous to be the one asked the questions. I dealt with some #ImposterSyndrome as I asked myself if I knew enough about manufacturing to be speaking in front of an audience. 

After some deep digging and #InnerWork, I decided to change the perspective of the interview. This wasn’t about me trying to sound or look #perfect. It was about me sharing my experiences running a #FamilyBusiness and how my experience would serve the women in manufacturing. Once I changed this speaking engagement as an opportunity to be in #Service of others, then my heart opened and I was able to speak my truth. 💓

My story of leaving #Hollywood to go into #Manufacturing inspired not only the other #WomenInMedTech, but also the men. Someone asked how can we inspire the next generation to continue to work in manufacturing as #Robotics and #AI are becoming more advanced? I don’t have an answer for that yet, but I’m committed to promoting manufacturing as #Fun #Cool & #Sexy 🤪🤓⚙️🦄🚀 #mdmwest2023 #medicaldesign #medtech #womenintech #womenin3dprinting

Current results ✨ 7 weeks into #75hard and I have 25 more days left. 

This challenge consists of: 

🤸🏋🏻‍♀️ 2x 45 min workouts a day, 1 of the workouts need to be outdoors 

💦 Drink 1 gallon of water 

🥗 Follow a diet, no alcohol 

📖 Read 10 pages of a non-fiction/self-development book 

📸 Take a progress photo 

Everyday. If I miss any of these tasks, I’ll need to start over. 

It’s taught me that doing simple things consistently can be so mundane, yet it’s very important to program repetitive skills into our daily lives if we want to become successful.  We can only get better at something when we do it over and over again. 

I recently became a member of the leadership group called @aretesyndicate and one of the founders @andyfrisella came up with this 75 Hard Challenge. It’s not a fitness challenge, but it’s a mental challenge with a bonus of a better physique at the end of the 75 days. 

I’ve never felt better mentally and physically. The reading portion is my favorite part of it! I’ve already gone through 3.5 books in almost 2 months. I’ll definitely add this to my daily routine after I’m done with the 75 days. 

Can’t wait to share more when I complete 75 Hard! ✨💪🏼💥 

#letsgo #mindset #biohacking #successmindset #entrepreneur

Happy National Manufacturing Day! 🙌🏼🇺🇸⚙️ 

So grateful for this industry that has made my life more meaningful. Being able to see our clients’ faces when they successfully assemble their projects with our machined parts makes my heart so full. 🥰

How does machining work? It starts with a block of raw material made of plastic or metal and we machine away material on our CNC until it matches an engineer’s CAD drawing with precise dimensions. That is called Subtractive Manufacturing (taking away material). 

Here, I’m holding a ramjet that was printed by @velo3d. They make industrial metal 3D printers that can make some really intricate parts that cannot be machined on a CNC. This ramjet 🚀 was started with metal powder that was melted together with lasers, layer by layer. This is called Additive Manufacturing (adding material). 

I can’t wait to share more about manufacturing with you on my upcoming podcast called “Making Things Fun, Cool, and Sexy”. 

Bookmark my website www.ChristineHolly.com and watch my podcast episodes there. (🔗 Link in bio). 

✨Silicon Valley Elite Manufacturing✨

What a great turnout and event for #CelebrateManufacturing at @hapasbrewing organized by @sfmade + @mfgsj! 🙌🏼✨

I proudly wore my @versace heels and @dior earrings + necklace to show how women can still be feminine in a masculine industry. 💁🏻‍♀️ 

It was great chatting with the Major of San Jose @mattmahansj about what #SiliconValleyEliteManufacturing does and how we appreciate the public sector’s support to help keep manufacturing in America. 

Major shoutout to my beautiful mom @kimoanh54, mfg badass @olive.elle, fellow @ambayarea board member Linda Sanchez from @casasanchezfoods, and my empowering gf @alisonangelis for coming out to support me. There were others in the industry who came out to support including @trinityautomation & #BrightLightWelding. 

Speaking in front of a crowd really fires me up. It empowers me to continue sharing my love of manufacturing to the community so more women and our next generation can see how rewarding mfg is. 

Up next, I’ll be speaking at local high schools to get the word out and inspire our children entering the workforce. 

Let’s not only bring manufacturing back to America. We need to KEEP it in California. Did you know California is the largest Manufacturing state in the US? 🇺🇸 Let’s continue to support local manufacturers so we can provide more jobs and contribute to decreasing homelessness in our state. 🙌🏼✨⚙️🇺🇸🐻 

The speech from tonight will be posted on YouTube soon! Keep an eye out for a post. ✨

If you told me a few years ago I’d leave Hollywood, embrace family legacy, get engaged and plan for my upcoming wedding, I would have laughed. Life’s curveballs are so real, but so is the power within us to weather storms and chase the truth. Sometimes, life demands everything – grit, resilience, and patience.
